p4
VThe 338tharadhanaof Sri Raghavendra Swamy was celebrated with utmost devotion andbhakthiin Hyderabad. Sangeetha Acharya Gururajachar who is 87, is a devotee of Sri Raghavendra Swamy and has been celebrating thearadhanafor more than 50 years now, giving importance to classical music where several musicians from city offer theirswaraarchanato the Swamy. Besides being a highly knowledgeable musician, he is also an excellent guru who has been relentlessly teaching music to many students. At his age he is fit and a never tiring musician and sings inoru katta sruthiwhich is amazing. The speed with which he sings is even more surprising and singing aswarakalpanato every item with perfection is his hallmark. His music is traditional and in fact he is the first musician to come to city in 1940s and since then he has been doing humble service to the world of music. He is known as &#8216;Bheeshma Pithamah&#8217; in music circles and a great Raghavendra Swamyupasaka.
